<action name=WORKDIR(2)>WORKDIR(2)</action>                                             <action name=WORKDIR(2)>WORKDIR(2)</action>

NAME
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            workdir - get the current working directory

SYNOPSIS
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            include "workdir.m"\;
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            workdir := load Workdir Workdir->PATH\;

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            init:  fn(): string\;

DESCRIPTION
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            Workdir returns a string representation of the working
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            directory of the invoking process.

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            When Inferno boots, the initial process has / for its
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            working directory.

SOURCE
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            /appl/lib/workdir.b

SEE ALSO
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            <action name=sys-chdir(2)>sys-chdir(2)</action>, <action name=sys-fd2path(2)>sys-fd2path(2)</action>, <action name=sys-stat(2)>sys-stat(2)</action>

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>                                Inferno Manual
